# CLAUDE.local.md — personal overrides

> Copy this file to `CLAUDE.local.md` (without `.example`) and edit.
> Add `CLAUDE.local.md` to your `.gitignore` so it stays personal.
> Per the kit standard: `personas.md` and `mvp-spec.md` are
> team-shared. `CLAUDE.local.md` is yours.

## Personal sandbox + test data

```
# Example — edit for your machine
SANDBOX_URL=http://localhost:8080
TEST_USER=alice@example.com
TEST_API_KEY=<see ~/.env-personal>
```

Reference these in conversation: "use my sandbox URL" → Claude
reads this file and substitutes.

## Personal preferences

```
- I prefer pnpm over npm. Don't use npm install in my sessions.
- My editor is helix; if you suggest editor commands, suggest helix
  bindings.
- I review PRs on phone; keep PR descriptions under 200 chars.
```

## Personal aliases / shortcuts

```
- "rev" → "use the brutal-reviewer subagent on the current build"
- "stop" → "block any code edit until I confirm — I'm planning"
```

## Notes from past sessions on this project

(Optional. Add things Claude has corrected you on or learned about
you that should persist. Or let auto-memory at
`~/.claude/projects/<project>/memory/MEMORY.md` handle this
automatically — see `methodology/CONTEXT-MANAGEMENT.md` § auto
memory.)

---

**Remember:** add `CLAUDE.local.md` to `.gitignore`. The kit's
`/init`-style setup does this automatically if you choose the
"personal" option.
